 ● I have identified several potential issues in the hyrule kernel module's self-unload mechanism triggered by Link's death, including missing taskqueue_drain, unreleased global locks, and risks with self-unloading from a taskqueue thread. The link_death test is currently failing, confirming that the self-unload mechanism is not working as expected, and I will next investigate this failure and implement necessary safeguards.                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               
