 ● The project is a FreeBSD kernel module 'hyrule'. I've reviewed last.log, which indicates a previous attempt to fix a kernel panic during self-unload when "Link dies". The current code in hyrule.c already includes many of the changes from the log, but hyrule_map.c is missing the educational stubs for character device operations ioctl, poll, etc.. The kernel panic is likely caused by the taskqueue thread returning to unmapped module code after calling kern_kldunload for self-unloading. I need to complete the stubs in hyrule_map.c and   
   find a safer way to handle self-unloading.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               
